caption: Service was excellent. Casey was fun, upbeat, and knowledgeable. Beer and food were excellent as well.

There is truly no other restaurant like Bixi. They offer a take on Asian-American cuisine unmatched by anyone else. In addition to dishes that are so delicious and surprisingly complex, the refreshing collection of beers brewed in house pair perfectly with every meal, regardless of which brew you choose. I personally love how the lemongrass and jasmine notes provide a fine tea experience to beer drinking. With the addition of super friendly and highly knowledgeable wait staff, this place is easily one of the best restaurants in Chicago.
Awesome food! Chicken sandwich is the bomb! Also happy to have the Owen & Engine options available. Well done, Bo!
Great drinks and food. Limited healthy options.
Never disappointed! The food is soooo good. Asian fusion done right.

saw that they carried the Owen and Engine Burger here so I rushed here on my bike to try it! They had a huge deal on Sunday which is buy two burgers and get a free growler. Definitely take advantage of that deal. I got the michigan getaway which was a saison with cherry and star anise. Did not get cherry notes but the anise was prominent, like root beer. I wish the saison was tart as this just tasted like an ale to me as I was expecting some tartness.  The burger though is what I really came for AND DID IT DELIVER. I have been searching for a burger better than au cheval and was hoping this would be the one. The aged cheddar was great and the caramelized onions really elevated this burger. Also the bun was fantastic as well, so soft and whatever was on top of the bread is great too. They bread was perfectly toasty that added a nice crunch to each bite. I'm personally not a fan of the thicc patty burgers but still a magnificent burger. If you like kuma corner's style of burger, this one is a must try!!!
Expensive but good!
Great food, great beer, great rooftop and atrium!
I don’t know how this place doesn’t have a higher rating. What a great meal- you will not be disappointed!!
Food fine. Staff incompetent. There was room inside downstairs, but they had us go upstairs and outside on a 40° windy night. Lack of common sense.

Pros: Food is good and my waiter really was  considerate of my vegan diet. Cons: Uncoscious bias treatment on the basis of race and sex. Management and the hostess invisibilized and dismissed me as a costumer. Management had an opportunity to be solution-otiented and honest, but chose not to. My experience before dining was stressful and onerous. I had a patio reservation for 8:00. I called 25 minutes prior to my reservation and told them me and my party of 2 were running 10 minutes behind. They said it was okay. When I arrived at the restaurant at 8:10 they said the table was still occupied even though the occupants had surpassed the maximum 2-hour time they could spend at a table. I patiently waited because they assured me that the occupants would be done in 5 minutes. 10 minutes later, I checked in to get an update (the entire time my friend and I didn't move from in front of the hostess podium and there was a guy not wearing a mask in the common area and no one said anything). They said the same thing as before. After 30 minutes of waiting and asking in 10 minute intervals. I was ready to leave, but there were no other restaurants in the area that had outdoor seating and that was important because we're quite conscious of COVID. Couldn't go home because we were celebrating my friend's engagement. After 30 minutes, I suggested a seat in a vacant area of the restaurant no thanks to management and we dined. There were so many customers that I saw get treated with respect and attentiveness that made it apparent that the treatment I received was because I was Black. I will not be dining or recommending this place to anyone.
Nice food for vegan also.  We have vegan dish in this time and it's pretty good for all of dishes

Amazing place for a delicious brunch with few friends and a lot of beer! Their Asian inspired dishes are delicious! The Thai beef was certainly my favorite. The ambiance is also pretty cool, with a huge bar area and a nice terrace.

The KFC deal was pretty good, and I enjoyed the beer. The sides were really good, especially the kimchi. However, the Thai sweet chili sauce was underwhelming. It was not that hot and resembled more of an orange chicken sauce with how tart the sauce was. I was hoping for more of a soy flavor so maybe I should’ve tried the Korean bbq sauce. The chicken was cooked perfectly and the ambiance is cool
The wings and coleslaw is just unreal. UNREAL. I will forever crave their wings. And the guys who work here are some hotties. All around. Great place to be 😝🤣

The cheeseburger here was very much on par with some of the more notoriously delicious burgers in the city, which makes this a Logan Square destination that really stands out. Equally impressive was how flavorful and savory their fried rice was; I can't think of many other places that execute this well with such variety.  As a huge Three Floyds fan I was super excited to try their collaborative beer, The Regionnaire, and it didn't disappoint. Atmosphere was really great on the inside but the second floor with the roof that opens up to the sky is definitely where I'd sit if given the choice. You could come here for dinner or just for the drinks and have a great time either way.
This place is BOMB!!! I'm so glad I stopped in. Portions are large and shareable. The Hotdogs are amazing! My wife  loved their tacos (taco picture not shown)
Beutifull restsurant you want eat and drink homemade beer

My favorite spot in Logan Square. The cocktails, beer and food is amazing. Everything we tried is top quality. The upstairs rooftop is a hidden gem. This is a must visit if you're in the Logan Square neighborhood. Also, it has probably the best beer selection in all of Chicago.
Everything on the menu is amazing, never disappoints!
Beautiful rooftop patio, Interesting beer and cocktail list, plus good food with some vegan options. A little pricey for Logan Square but thats the way things seem to be trending in the area
Great Atmosphere, great service, great food, great beer
Great food, great drink.

It was okay. Went there late on a Thursday night for drinks and a snack/desert after eating dinner elsewhere. There were only about 4 tables and yet service was slow. The beers were very underwhelming and the mixed drink my girlfriend got was disgusting. But for desert we got the Chocolate Sundae and it was pretty dang good.
One of my favorite go-tos in the neighborhood! A very extensive and unique menu and delicious beer to go with.
Great atmosphere, good place to go out at night. Very sleek style. Their brewed beers were alright.
Food and service are both great Beautiful rooftop in the summer.
Liked the drinks and atmosphere.  Food needs help on many levels.  The sweet potato steamed bun was very dry and way over priced....
Super cute space - not what I expected for a place with Beer in the name. Food was super interesting - but the tatse were a little heavy and definitely thinkers ...event space is so fun...
Great food and beer.
Great food....delicious. super presentation. Scarrrrrrry pictures!
We went around 1pm for lunch during restaurant week and turns out they cancelled their lunch menu? Would have been nice to know ahead of time bee ended up getting appetizers and went somewhere else.
This food was out of this world, so imaginative and each bite delicious

Went for brunch and tried the Lamb Wontons and Mac and Cheese.  The wontons were amazing!! The breakfast cocktail called Bad & Bixi was really good. Vodka, grapefruit syrup, Cava, and something else I'd never heard of called Besk. Came for lunch yesterday and the Drunken Noodles were out of this world. Highly recommend this place if you're in the area. If you aren't, it's worth the Uber ride!!

This place rocks for dim sum/brunch, but they took the best dish off the menu. Bring back the seafood lo mein! I am dead serious! I brought my friend group here, my girlfriend here, my parents here... they took the lo mein off and I’ve been back once. Correlation implies causation in this case, bring it back!!

Food was great. Interesting concept of Asian food with beer but totally works for me. Chicken sandwich was tasty and the nuts they serve are amazing. I even took some home. Had a lager with lunch which I thought was just ok. Otherwise I'm pretty impressed.
Fried rice, although supposedly popular, is not great. Potstickers are strangely fried on one side only and seem undercooked on the other side. Spicy fries are decent, but quite salty
Try the bao burger and pork belly abodo dishes!

The atmosphere was awesome! The restaurant was decorated very well. There is a ton of space in the venue. We had a reservation but we could have walked in if we wanted to. The beer was really refreshing. Most of there beers are brewed with teas so they are very smooth. The food was good but it was a little too spicy for me. I wish that I knew it was going to be that spicy before I ordered.
Flavorful and inventive takes on traditional cuisine. You need to try the Szechuan peanuts!! Gai lan, potstickers of all sorts, haven’t had the whole fish but it looks amazing!
Food excellent.  Service fine. Beer so-so....
Great food!
(Translated by Google) At Logan Plaza, Bixi Beer uses a beer with Sichuan peppercorn and cardamom ingredients to pair its own Asian cuisine.  (Original) 在洛根广场，Bixi Beer用加了四川花椒和小豆蔻成分的啤酒来配自家的亚洲料理。

Beer was not to my taste at all, extremely underwhelming. The inside is designed more for Instagram than because of any kind of sense of style or identity. The people were very nice and the food was solid. But there are other breweries that can do you a whole lot better. Move along, beer drinkers!
Good staff good food.
Upstairs is so beautiful.  Full glass ceiling, plants & trees abound.  Brussel sprout salad with pears is delicious. (they do charge for employee insurance)

Delicious food, nice waitstaff and bartenders. For a casual restaurant, however, it's pricey -- like $8 for bar peanuts pricey. And that's before the 2% surcharge. (If patrons don't like it, they're directed to tell a staff member they don't want to pay for the employee's healthcare. I guess BiXi's shareholders don't like paying overhead 🙄 Why isn't there also a light bulbs, paperclips, and silverware surcharge?).  This could be a great pick for special occasions, but then again you could could always eat like a king at a Chinatown BYOB restaurant with roundtrip ride share fares for about the same cost as dinner for two at BiXi.

Overall very good experience! From the excellent service to the amazing food and special beers they offer. Everything was timely and didn’t take long to come out despite how busy it was. Highly recommend!

Xmas eve dinner.  The food was a cut above, not just bar food, but a cut above the linen table cloths on the neighborhood.   The roast suckling pig was delicious.   The coffee stout and the sour farmhouse were something special.  The service was outstanding.   The portions incredibly generous. Bottom line, a superior experience.
Thai Basil Beef was outstanding! Every dish was a memorable taste experience. The beers were all very good and the Asian twist made them all standout especially the Voidwalker pale ale w lychee.
Great food, even better ambiance. Don’t snooze on the upstairs either. Asian-fused brews and menu will leave you aching to come back

Where else can you find a unique mix of bar experience and tasty pan Asian food in Chicago? I am surprised how well they go together! Saw this place on TV and just had to give it a try - turns out we had to go back-to-back for two nights. It’s that good.  Try everything. They are all good. As a typical Taiwanese who loves food would say, there’s no landmine to step on. :D

Beautiful atmosphere. Can make any visit special. Different spaces in restaurant each have their own personality and experience. Rooftop is open and great in summer. They also have back party room.  The dinners are large and good to share after enjoying several appetizers. Especially recommend the kung boa chicken. Great cocktails too; so good I haven't had their beer!
Amazing food, staff, and most importantly beer! I would highly recommend the Bao Burger and the Brussel Sprout Salad! Super tasty 😋

Everything we had here was amazing. I can't rave about this place enough, we ordered most of the 1st plate appetizers, a few dishes I didn't even know what they would look like and everything was exceptional.  Will definitely come back here next time I'm in Chicago!

The spot is great with a nice terrace upstairs.  Food is solid as well.

This place is incredible. The food is outstanding. And the 2nd floor dining area is spectacular. The have a retractable roof, so you're partially outside (on a nice night). The drinks were incredible. I especially enjoyed the pork crepe and the noodles. Everything was unique - everyone at our table loved every single item that we ordered!
Gorgeous atmosphere with retractable roof and lush furnishings.  Food has fresh herbal authentic Asian roots with a modern twist.  Service and staff were disappointing.
Upstairs views and decor are something to see. Extremely well done. Food is great.

Good beers, interesting and different flavor notes like jasmine rice. Potstickers were amazing! Honestly the best we've had as well as the sauces. Wish we hadn't eaten before coming here, definitely coming back soon for a full meal.

Amazing brunch! Initially came here for a beer and passport stamp but so glad we did brunch. For a group of 3 we ordered 6 dishes (everything sounded so good) and it was more than enough food! Highly recommend the seafood lo mein, shrimp and crab dip and fried rice. Great atmosphere, heard the upstairs was great but didn't get a chance to check it out. Awesome atmosphere, but service was pretty slow and the entrees were lacking. Menu descriptions were misleading. We ordered both of the hot oil noodles and didn’t realize that they were literally JUST in hot oil, no other kind of sauce, which made the dishes very heavy. Starters were delicious. I love the design and theme of this place. The upstairs and roof top are fun, but the main dining room is so cozy and intimate it's perfect for a date night! While you're there make sure to get the Malort slushies, it's delicious.

Second time to BiXi Beer, this time for a post- wedding dinner.  We passed lots of delicious small plates. The drinks and beer were great and,  while I didn't try it,  I heard the burger pronounced the best EVER by those who tried it.  Server was awesome.

Not a great option for vegetarians, but the dishes that they do have are pretty tasty. I especially enjoyed the crepe with the mushroom and kimchi dumplings. The dishes are about $10 per dish, but are quite filling and you don’t need to order too many items. I would come back here again.

I went to this place three times in one weekend, so you could say that I liked it a lot. The Salted Cucumber Cider is awesome. Their beef fat fries and szechuan peanuts are great appetizers and perfect amount for sharing. The Pork Belly Adobo was absolutely amazing. 10/10 would order again. One of my friends got the fried rice. It was a perfect small portion and tasted incredible. Kimchi Mandu's are definitely a do. The Half order of the Ssam plate is perfect for sharing between 3 people. Bottom line, don't sleep on this place.

Really incredible rooftop space. The open roof, breezy single room space, and effective interior decor made for a summer-in-a-palace feel.  The drink list was a good size without being overwhelming. The beer list is about 2/3rds house-made beer and the rest a selection of interesting guest pours. The Unspoken Rule golden ale was easily the winner amongst their own beers, while a Salted Cucumber Dry Cider from Stem Ciders was a real showstopper on a hot summer day.  The cocktail list was small but effective,  offering a delicious half dozen original summer cocktails each focused on a different liquor, as well as two frozen options that looked great.  The food was the real winner though. A long list of small Firsts will tempt you with a wide range of options, followed by half the number of mains. You'll probably want a First and Second per person.  The Shrimp and Crab Dip is a must, though, served with beautifully full and perfectly crisped wonton chips for scooping up the herbed dip and catching some of the sweet chili oil in the bottom of the bowl. We also tried the Chicago Beef Bao, which I found underwhelming; it came across as a pretty straight and somewhat uninteresting Chicago beef sandwich shoved into a really mediocre bao bun.  For the Seconds, the hot oil noodles are a killer bargain. One of the cheaper options on the menu, it comes in a large bowl filled with a large mound of this massive coiled noodle soaked with flavorful oils and decked out in all sorts of delicious toppings. It has some heat that quickly builds over time, but nothing prohibitive or painful, sticking the landing in that perfect zone where your taste buds are being pushed to the edge and you can't stop yourself from wanting to get closer and closer.  The pork belly was a real winner too, arriving gorgeously cooked and scoured. Cutting into it, the texture is heavenly with the right mix of meaty resistance and pillowy fat, but the flavor of it all mixed with the sauce at its base make for a truly sublime dish.  Can't wait to go back and try more things.

Drinks were delicious and varied. The beer was cold and they brewed their own in house. The food was phenomenal and the portions were huge. I got the adobo pork belly and it was so good I was awe struck. This place also has a rooftop deck which looked very cool. Very excited to visit this place again.
Always amazing!

The food was not bad but not worth waiting 30+ minutes on 4th of July lunch with 95+degree weather, I don’t think they are fully staffed and we were barely served to be honest, btw the belt noodles taste okay but way too heavy and oily, don’t recommend the food unless you wanna stop by at their “popular” rooftop space for a drink and taking pics
Great rooftop and amazing drinks.

Tasty food, tasty beer, and a very cool atmosphere. The first floor is nice, but the second floor is such a lovely surprise. It's light and airy with a beautiful patio and a couple of interesting interior rooms tucked away. This space would be great for a private event. I really like this new addition to the neighborhood.
A little pricey, but a lot of options. Delicious! Fun! Really good food, a lot of drink choices. They can make a lot of what's on the menu vegetarian

Come here quite frequently since they've opened.  Left a very different, very positive review 6 months ago but sadly my experience has changed so my review and rating must change. The kitchen here is PAINFULLY slow at any time of day. I've routinely waited 30-45 minutes for fries when I was the only guest there. Most recently, 35 minutes for fries and 45 minutes for a chicken sando; 10 customers, only three of us eating. And the bartender seemed annoyed when I asked him to check on my food. I think I've had my fill of Bixi Beer. Not for people with a schedule to keep.

(4 stars bc service is still pretentious and slow (standard for the neighborhood))  Beer is 3rd rate. Roof top is meh. Trike has better Asian food. Great beer!

Yo. Decent atmosphere, great food, suuuper friendly staff. Overall fun experience, but something about the vibe just doesn’t click with me. It felt a little contrived, and—while the food was good—it felt a little pretentious and overpriced for what it really was.
Coolest rooftop bar ever. Plus, pretty solid beers, including a few that hit the unique tinge just enough!

Exquisite dim sum in the heart of Logan Square. I particularly enjoyed the tuna tartare. The lamb belt noodles were a little too heavy for my palate, but cooked exquitely with big bold flavors. Sit on the roof where the afternoon light pours in.
This place is very stylish, the beer and food were great. My only complaint is that there wasn't any music playing, which to me was a bummer, I went there on a Wednesday.
Great beer. Will be returning.
Nice place, friendly staff, a little over priced for Logan

Such a fun instagramable place for brunch! I had made reservations for 4 of us and then expanded it to 6 with no problems. Easy to make the reservations online. We were seated immediately for at a long table in the upstairs room. The upstairs room had a glass roof so it was beautiful to get to see the outside but it was a pain after awhile when the sun was shining down directly on you. We had all checked in on Yelp and had gotten the free beers which were a pleasant surprise. They have a good selection and mix of light and dark beers.  For the brunch portion, they have some great options but okay options for vegetarian. I was surprised at how rigid the menu seemed to be (for example, the noodle dish could not be made vegetarian). For our vegetarian counterparts, they got the bubble waffle, kimchi mandu, the eggplant bao brunch, the fried rice and beer bread. It was a good amount of food but did leave people feeling hungry a few hours later. For those of us who ate meat, we had the lamb wontons, the classic breakfast and the drunken noodle. Great dishes and I would recommend the lamb wontons for sure and also the BEER BREAD (this was AMAZING).  The reason why this place stayed at a 3 star for me and not a 4 star is because despite the atmosphere, I did not think the food was elevated to an asian fusion status but rather just asian food. Also for the quantity of food, definitely priced more than it deserved. A few reviewers have also mentioned the employee insurance fee which I wasn't a huge fan of. I am all for employee insurance benefits but I do not think that it is at the responsibility of the patron vs the employer. I think it is quite tacky to have it added to my bill. The option of opting out is to "ask your server" but that just seems rude. At the end of the day, 2% does not make a huge difference in my bill and if I can help out a hardworker, I will gladly do so. But to have the dishes priced highly and then on top of that, have the 2% already added was a bit of a turn off.
Excellent food, great service, amazing atmosphere especially upstairs outside on a mildly breezy summer-like day.
LAMB WONTONS. So amazing.
The retractable roof brought in a pleasant breeze. The cocktails are well above average.

We loved it here! Super interesting beers! Our two favorites were brewed with tea! I loved a Jasmine tea beer (Golden Rule) which was light and so easy drinking with the mellow flavor of Jasmine throughout. My finance loved a beer brewed with Mango and Black tea, which we took home a growler of ($24ish) It was very slightly bitter with delicious notes of black tea and mango. We tried all of the brews they make in house (except the one IPA on tap, as we are not fans) and liked every one. Full wall of spirits if you'd prefer a mixed drink as well as guest taps and frozen cocktails! There was a good size dining area and a bar that runs the depth of the space. We did not eat but the menu looks incredible! Seafood tower!! There is an upstairs party room that can be rented I would assume. Male, female, and, unisex bathrooms available downstairs. We can't wait to go back!
Try their vietnamese coffee!

If you like spicy food, this will be your place. 👌
Bringing the River North crowd to Logan.

Everything was great! Best tuna tartar we’ve ever had, the lamb wontons, pot stickers, and fried green tomato boa buns were also amazing! Can’t wait to go back.

This is a great addition to the neighborhood. The beer is awesome and food is amazing!
I love everything about this place. Great food, great beer, and there are two levels with an upstairs patio.

Overall: Bixi Beer provides a fresh option for boozy brunches and group-style dinners.  The good: They brew their own beers which are actually really tasty. They cover all the bases - sours, ales, lagers, stouts, each one great. Plus, you get a free check-in from one of their drafts. The atmosphere is sophisticated with white tiles and black accents but the vibe and food offerings don't necessarily match, which is a very good thing. I loved the plant accents as well, which brought the tone down. As for the food, it's typically a dim-sum kind of fashion, but our table did a more "get your own meal" and everything was great. Drunken noodles, eggs, fried rice, it was all hot and flavorful.  The not-so-good: A little price and the seating was a little uncomfortable for our particular booth, but neither are much to complain about. And, the house-made sausage wasn't particularly to my liking.  Food/drink: 8/10 Atmosphere: 8/10 Service: 9/10
Beers were light and smooth AF
Good Asian inspired food and solid drinks.  Friendly bar service.  Their baos are the best part.

The Panang Curry and Mezcal cocktail far exceeded any expectations that I had. I sampled all 8 of their current draft beers and really liked about 50% of them. That said, I believe they are all well crafted. I will definitely be back for more of everything.
Unique spot with terrific brews! Easy to get to via public trans, too.
(Translated by Google) Good place to buy and distract with the games of the machines  (Original) Buen lugar para comprar y distraerse con los juegos de las máquinas

Inventive menu, friendly staff, nice space for group dinners. The cocktails are spot on with clever combinations. Sitting at the bar for dinner is a great options, as we locals like to do, with a book or a crossword  puzzle (saw both going on while there...). Try it out, you'll be happy you did.
The eggplant bao is out of this world good. Btwn beer and food, feeling like we stumbled upon a real gem with this spot.
Very great atmosphere and the food was very tasty and filling.

If you're looking for something interesting and more importantly GOOD, go check out this place. Amazing house brewed beers and the food simply  can't be found anyplace else. You'll thank yourself for stopping in.
Very classy pot! Food is amazing. MUST get the cheeseburger Bao. Delicious frozen cocktails.
Tasty!  Tasty!  Tasty!  The whole fish was out of this world!  The raw oysters from both the East and West coast were delicious.  Mango salad was amazing!  I can't wait to go back and try more.

Absolutely loved it. Amazing food, flavor and ambiance. Every bite was a lean back, chew and savor experience. I'm not a big beer drinker, however i found a couple on the menu that i could have regularly. Can't wait to check out the rooftop when the weather stops being ignorant. BiXi has definitely made an impression on me. 💪🏾💪🏾
This place is great. The service and the meals are awesome

Went for restaurant week and loved the space and great service. The burger wasn’t my favorite, but the apps and bubble waffles were soo good. We sat upstairs which was almost like a greenhouse with the glass ceiling and walls, it was like being on a patio in winter! The hot Thai coffee was so good. Will definitely be back to try their beer and dinner. The matcha ice cream was tasty (picture), but the real winner was the butterscotch blondie on top.

I liked "bee-she" a lot.  Beer variety was good.  All styles were well represented with some very interesting twists that paired nicely with the food.  There was a few I would buy a crowler to go, but mainly the beers were well matched for the food.  Wife and I shared a flight of all of them.  Definitely not cheap.  Cocktails were well made.  Didn't try them all, but tasted a good sampling.  The slushie one I had was good, will want more during summer.  The belt noodles are kind of their specialty.  I recommend getting them.  Probably my favorite dish.  Whole fish was just ok.  Lots of other places around town have similar dishes.  Bixi's sauce was a little tired.  Lamb wontons were fantastic.  Would eat again.  Crab spread was basically denconstructed crab Rangoon. Good but meh.  Kimishi fried dumplings were quite nice, is eat those again.  All in all, some good menu items, a few meh things that could be reworked or tweaked to make special.  I'll be back to try more though.  Good addition to the area.
I was impressed by both the food and the beer.   I had the hoppy Amber and the wife had the sour ale.  Both excellent.
Food that leaves you speechless and a vibe that's intimate and relaxed. Incredible service to to things off, I can't wait to go back!
Fantastic place! The beers are excellent and the Asian inspired food is really good. I had Drunken Noodles for lunch, the kind of entree you don't normally find at a brewery. I'll definitely be back.

I visited Bixi Beer for Chicago Restaurant Week and the food was amazing! Everything my party ordered was so tasty that I am planning to come back here for my brother's 30th birthday dinner. My only issue is the service. The food came out very slow but I guess it takes time to create perfection right?
Good ambiance. Food is average.
Tasty drinks and food. Tried a very nice sour beer with citrus and a delicious eggplant bao.

Cool space. Great Beers and cocktails. Brunch food needs work, breakfast sandwich was ok, but not much different than a sandwich I recently had at Wendy's. Cant wait to try more Dim Sum though, that was delicious.
I recommend this place, good service.

Brunched with a large group. Kitchen handled our giant order flawlessly. Everything we ate was 100% delicious. My favorites were the tuna tartare, vietnamese crepe, beef bao, and oyster omelet. Fantastic experience, amazing food, beautiful space.
Definitely Not a good choice for native Chinese. Terrible food, stomach is very uncomfortable after eating rigid lamb wanton....... But the service is good
Place looks dirty, staff need to be more educated on what they serve

One of the most unique and upscale (yet approachable) breweries I've seen on my travels. Good variety of beer styles which were solid, and our two apps were very tasty. Wait staff super friendly and efficient. Very unassuming from outside yet modern feel inside. If upstairs open, seemed to be quieter. Great find.

Stopped in on a whim after getting my teeth cleaned. Delightful. The seafood lo mein is thick and creamy, not what I'm used to, and it was absolutely amazing. The selection of beers was great. There weren't many hoppy styles, but the styles they do, they execute very well. I had a flight, and my favorites were Shifties (crisp rice lager) and Train of Thought (delicious, roasted imperial coffee stout).

This is by far the best food I’ve had around Logan Square! The Dim Sum plates are an amazing value for the portion. The seafood lo mein was packed with flavor and huge chunks of lobster. The beers had unique flavor profiles, and the flight was a great value. Will definitely be back!
Cool place. Decent beer selection.

BiXi Beer was a great spot to have a casual brunch. Atmosphere, service and staff were excellent and the reasonably priced menu offered a variety of creative pan Asian dishes and cocktails (I recommend going with friends, sharing multiple appetizers and an entree or two). Highly recommend the Bubble Waffle Dish and the Thai Beef if you like spicy food. The Vietnamese Egg Rolls and Bao (not pictured) were also good.

I found this place out of the blue and was very pleasantly surprised. Visited for brunch with some friends and the restaurant interior is low key beautiful. I liked the vibe when I walked in instantly but when the host thought me upstairs, I was sold.  We ordered the Spicy Fried Chicken Sando which got thumbs ups all around the table. We also tried 2 of the baos which were pretty good, but also pretty pricey for such a small serving. The Oyster Omelette was very good; simple in essence but tasted was on point. Don't skip out on the dessert for sure because we shared a Matcha Chocolate ice cream sundae and it was delicious!  Definitely going back, and for sure in the summer!

Delicious, delicious beer. Unique and flavorful! "Will of the Thousands" was awesome as was the jasmine tea infused one. Cocktail bar was good too as are the appetizers. Art and atmosphere are cool too.
Food and beer were excellent. The service was extremely slow during my second visit, however.
We love this place. Great beers, lots of flavor not a lot of hops.  Fantastic food! I especially love the cheeseburger bao.  When it’s warm the roof deck is nice, secluded but outside.
Terrific food and service!
Great atmosphere, food & drinks!
This is an interesting experience! I love the service and the food was great! They also had an amazing coffee stout on tap!
Loved the food more than the beer actually. Service was great and liked the vibe of the place.
Can't wait to go back!

The beers here were great and a bit out of the box, e.g., Szechuan peppers, tea pearls, and the decor on the main floor was very cool. Did not get food this time around, but will definitely be back. Bartender was really helpful and quick.
Great food. Unique menu, cozy ambiance. Loved the drunken noodles and the brussel sprout salad. The coffee was not good. Stick to beer.
Great drinks, great beer, fancy good food and amazingly good and friendly service. As simple as that.
Overpriced and the beer tasted rancid.
Bok choy/noodle was amazing. Good beer too
Good gluten free options, brunch, love the upstairs

First time stopping in and the food was incredible.  All dishes are made to share which is always great in my opinion because it give me an excuse to try more items.  The beers are great too which is good since it is a brewery!

This place is great. Food selection for brunch was awesome. Great place to go and share meals. The beers are very different, but very good. Good selection of full bar too. The service was very warm and friendly. All around a great addition to a crowded market.
The food here is wonderful, I'm just not sure if I'm sold on their beers. They're fine beers, just not my cup of tea.
All the food was great
The vegetable belt udon was great.
Fantastic food and service
Good food and cocktails in nice, modern digs.
High end brewery and restaurant. Beautifully done. High tech brewing. Excellent food. Grand event space. Wonderful views of Logan Square.
Awesome vegan options and good beer
Good space, nice people and good beer.  Interesting wallpaper in Men's room.
Potstickers were amazing! Broth in the duck noodle soup was flavorful
Great place

This is my second time here - once for dinner, and today, brunch; neither of which I or my friends have been satisfied. Let's talk abt today.  We are here for my cousin's birthday, all excited abt the Asian fusion food. Here are some of the issues:  1) food size: in no world, Asian or or otherwise, would anyone sell ONE bao for that price point. That's terrible.  2) food service: we ordered quite a bit on the menu and when the food arrived, frites were cold and when we pointed it out, they said they were out of fries and don't have a microwave to heat up the fries. Yes.  A restaurant ran out of fries and don't have a microwave. Also, our order of siu mai never arrived even though we reminded them. Also, their Vietnamese coffee is thin, cloyingly sweet and merely ok. So expect overpriced food,a small quantities and the possibility that they food don't arrive or arrive cold. The egg tart, bao and scallion pancake did taste good, just to be fair  3) PRICE ON MENU DIDNT MATCH CHECK: I was really ok with all the issues above. But what really made my blood boil was that the prices on the menu didn't match the check. We had 2 items that were overcharged. You would have expected that with all the issues above-we did respectfully share our feedback- that they would savor the last chance to turn the sinking ship around. But nope. They took 3 dollars off and called it a day. Then the manager had the audacity to say, hope to see you again. Maybe it is my fault that a restaurant would go out of their way to fix it - maybe they are having a bad day-  but it was disappointing, that they didn't care. So please check your checks. You may be overpaying without realizing.  In sum, don't bother coming. Food is mediocre, they may charge you more than what is stated on the menu and the value of money is poor. Stay away.

Beer was solid, interesting flavor profiles. Food, Asian-inspired.  Our waitress lacked a bit of social finesse and general Asian food knowledge when describing the dishes. As a SE Asian, I was trying to ascertain specific information to decide between dishes to order. Also, the long singular noodle dish (awesome, tasty, concept), failed in execution due to WAY too much oil in the bottom of the bowl. An unnecessary amount of oil ruined the overall mouth-feel and taste of the noodle dish. The potstickers were good, you get 4 in total (forgot to picture). My friend ordered the vegan soup, not impressive in flavor. Would we return? Yes, probably for the beer and less complex food. Nice ambiance inside, and a cool black and white city skyline mural behind the bar!
This place Rules.
Beautiful atmosphere, especially upstairs. Friendly staff, interesting menu items. Would definitely come back
Great food, fun beers. I'll definitely be back
Stunningly beautiful space (be sure to check out the upstairs) with friendly service, excellent beer, and delicious food.
Great and unique take on food. The beer and food are amazing! Try the lamb dumplings- they are new to the menu.
So great! Server Shane knew his stuff and was perfect. Favorite order was the  ssam plate. Also reasonably priced.
Great service
